body:
Hi there. I have been struggling with a problem handling touch events using a SkiaSharp SKGLView in Xamarin.Forms. Here is a simple piece of test code to illustrate my problem. 

```c#
    public class TestCanvasView : SKGLView
    {
        private SKSurface _surface;
        private SKCanvas _canvas;

        public TestCanvasView()
        {
            HorizontalOptions = LayoutOptions.CenterAndExpand;
            VerticalOptions = LayoutOptions.CenterAndExpand;
            HeightRequest = 200;
            WidthRequest = 200;
            EnableTouchEvents = true;

            PaintSurface += OnCanvasViewPaintSurface;
        }

        private void OnCanvasViewPaintSurface(object sender, SKPaintGLSurfaceEventArgs e)
        {
            _surface = e.Surface;
            _canvas = _surface.Canvas;
            _canvas.DrawRect(new SKRect(0,0,CanvasSize.Width, CanvasSize.Height), new SKPaint{Color = Color.DarkSeaGreen.ToSKColor()});
        }

        protected override void OnTouch(SKTouchEventArgs e)
        {
            base.OnTouch(e);
        }
    }
```

Now this renders my DarkSeaGreen block just fine, but the OnTouch method is only called when I tap on the top left quadrant of the View. Essentially only 1/4 of the view is touch-sensitive. When I try to add a Xamarin.Forms GestureRecognizer, the same problem occurs. If I change this code to use an SKCanvasView, the touch events fire perfectly. 

This is on UWP, btw, I haven't been able to check it yet on any other platforms.
